is needed for non\-default installations where the admin port has been set up on
a port other that 8091.
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.sp
To retrieve the backup service settings:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
$ couchbase\-cli backup\-service \-c 127.0.0.1:8091 \-u Administrator \-p password \(rs
  settings \-\-get
\-\- Backup service configuration \-\-
History rotation size: 70 MB
History rotation period: 28 days
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
To set the backup service configuration use the \f(CR\-\-set\fP flag and any of the configuration flags for example:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
$ couchbase\-cli backup\-service \-c 127.0.0.1:8091 \-u Administrator \-p password \(rs
  settings \-\-set \-\-history\-rotation\-size 70 \-\-history\-rotation\-period 365
SUCCESS: Backup service settings set
.fi
